rComments: Review is for CML 3156B. Sylvia is a great professor. The course had multiple written assignments which Sylvia provided feedback on. She created a comfortable environment which which was important because the course was heavily discussion-based. There was no cold-calling, but participation was very much encouraged. I highlight recommend the course.

rComments: Prof Rich's lectures can be a little scattered at times, but she has a demonstrable knowledge base, clearly cares about students, and is always available to clarify things. Good discussions.

Dr. Rich's passion for criminal law shines through her teaching and made me exciting to come to class each week. She was aware of the unique circumstances of zoom learning and adjusted her course load accordingly. She likes when students are engaged and participating, so it helps to understand the readings before class and come with some questions.
Terrible lecturer but classes are mandatory. Cares about students
